# Sextant sidecar image build context filter.
#
# The build context is the repo root (so the Dockerfile can COPY from
# both `clients/typescript/` and `images/sidecar/entrypoint/`). This
# file trims everything else — every Go cache, every node_modules, every
# unrelated dir — so `docker build` doesn't ship the whole repo to the
# daemon.
#
# Pattern syntax: docker-style globs. `!` re-includes a previously
# excluded path. We start by excluding everything and re-include only
# what the Dockerfile actually COPYs.

# Default: drop everything.
*

# Re-include the two trees the Dockerfile needs.
!clients/typescript
!images/sidecar/entrypoint

# Drop the heavy/transient subdirs inside those trees so they don't
# bloat the build context (npm installs run inside the image; tests
# aren't needed in the image; pre-built dist/ for @sextant/client IS
# needed and is produced by `make ts-build` before `make sidecar-image`
# runs `docker build`).
clients/typescript/node_modules
clients/typescript/test
clients/typescript/coverage
clients/typescript/*.tsbuildinfo
images/sidecar/entrypoint/node_modules
images/sidecar/entrypoint/dist
images/sidecar/entrypoint/*.tsbuildinfo

# Always exclude version control and editor noise even from the
# re-included trees.
**/.git
**/.DS_Store
**/.idea
**/.vscode
**/*.swp
